# 🌍 IoT Based Environmental Monitoring System

## About the project

This project is about monitoring environmental conditions using IoT.
We used different sensors to check things like air quality, gas leakage, temperature and humidity in real time.

The system shows data in two ways:

* on an LCD (directly on the device)
* on a dashboard (phone/laptop)

We also tried to make it a bit smarter by showing simple suggestions instead of just numbers.

---

## What it does

* Measures air quality (MQ135)
* Detects gas leakage (MQ2 / MQ6)
* Reads temperature and humidity (DHT11/22)
* Shows data on LCD
* Sends data to cloud
* Gives basic warnings (like gas leak or bad air)

---

## Components used

**Hardware:**

* ESP8266 / ESP32
* MQ135 (air quality sensor)
* MQ2 / MQ6 (gas sensor)
* DHT11 / DHT22
* 16x2 LCD
* Buzzer
* Wires + breadboard

**Software:**

* Arduino IDE
* ThingSpeak / Blynk (for dashboard)

---

## How it works

1. Sensors read data continuously
2. ESP processes the values
3. Data is shown on LCD
4. Same data is sent to cloud using WiFi
5. Dashboard updates in real time
6. If something is wrong (like gas leak), buzzer turns on

---

## Parameters monitored

* Temperature (°C)
* Humidity (%)
* Air Quality (AQI / PPM)
* Gas level (PPM)

---

## Extra thing we added

Instead of only showing numbers, we added small messages like:

* “Air quality is good”
* “Air quality is poor, avoid going outside”
* “Gas leakage detected, check immediately”

So even a normal person can understand easily.

---

## Setup (basic idea)

* Install Arduino IDE
* Connect sensors to ESP
* Upload code
* Add WiFi details in code
* Open dashboard link

---

## Problems we faced

* MQ sensors were not stable at first
* Needed calibration
* WiFi connection sometimes drops
* Sensor readings fluctuate

---

## Future improvements

* Add mobile app
* Add more sensors (PM2.5 etc.)
* Better accuracy
* Use machine learning for prediction

